The Belgian soccer federation yesterday said they had started an inquiry into allegations that several players in the country s top league, including Warriors striker Knowledge Musona bet on their matches. BY HENRY MHARA In a statement, the federation launched the investigations on Thursday last week, a day after club Waasland Beveren fired keeper Laurent Henkinet for betting on a match in which he featured.Belgian media have confirmed that four or five players were involved in betting on their matches including Musona, who plays for KV Oostende being one of them. Investigations have been started to see whether certain players have infringed federation regulations, the federation said.The regulations forbids players, managers and officials from betting on matches in which they or their club participate.If found guilty, Musona and his co-accused could be fined although other reports suggest the offense carries a criminal charge attracting at least five years in prison.